         Biggest problem with DoT stacking as I see it .. is exploits.. </P><P>If they implement DoT stacking What’s to say I can’t stack 3 dots then zone, zone back and stack 3 dots and again zone etc etc etc ..  what if 3 Necro’s do this?? Big ass exploit Game is changed,, for the worse .. </P><P>One possible fix / solution / workaround to the DoT stacking issues would be to tag DoTs Race and Diety specific: (not even sure if this is possible)</P><P>Identical DoT s just named differently </P><P>Funeral Pyre would change to ..</P><P>Dark Elf – Dark Funereal<BR>Erudite – Forehead Funereal<BR>Gnome – Sawed off Funereal<BR>Human – Pasty Funereal<BR>Iksar – Scaly Funereal</P><P>… after it was scribed.</P><P>That way they stack since the npc sees them as different but each individual Necro would not be individually more powerful or be able to exploit. </P><P>So If ya had 3 Necro’s on a raid .. say A Human A DE and a Iksar they could all cast say .. Splurt and FP and they would all stack … not perfect but better than current.</P><P>You would have to increase the # of DoTs that a NPC could have cast on it. </P><P>Just a thought … </P><P><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
